User: Write JavaScript to disable a button with the ID "processBtn" after it has been clicked once.

<thinking>
The user wants to disable a button after a click. I'll add a click event listener to the button, and within the handler, I'll set the button's `disabled` property to `true`.
</thinking>

<blueprint>
// JavaScript DOM manipulation
Test 'disable_button_on_click' {
  const button = document.getElementById('processBtn');
  button.addEventListener('click', () => {
