User: Write JavaScript to create an `<img>` element, set its `src` to "image.jpg", and append it to a `<div>` with the id "image-container".

<thinking>
The user wants to dynamically create and add an image to the page. I'll use `document.createElement` to create the `<img>` element, set its `src` attribute, and then append it to the specified container div.
</thinking>

<blueprint>
// JavaScript DOM manipulation
Test 'create_and_append_image' {
  const img = document.createElement('img');
  img.src = 'image.jpg';
  const container = document.getElementById('image-container');
  container.appendChild(img);
}
</blueprint>
